      "content": "i get what u mean about the risk but i really cant afford a doctor visit right now and it doesn't even look that deep if i stop the oozing. i've seen plenty of people use manuka honey for skin stuff and it works great. if i just clean it really well with antiseptic first and then apply a thick layer of honey to keep it moist, is there really any reason i can't just do that at home instead of risking the expense at a clinic?",
